        <bioghist id="ref35">
            <head>Biographical/Historical note</head>
            <p>Donald Martin was drafted into the U.S. Navy in the spring of 1944. He received a specialized training as a navy hospital corpsman. He stationed in the Naval Hospital in Bethesda, MD and then was reassigned overseas to the Navy Military Hospital #204 at Tinian Island. He was discharged as a Pharmacist's Mate 2nd class by the end of May 1946. He then returned to Penn State to continue his studies as an industrial engineer, at which time he also joined a reserve unit. He was called to report for duty in Sept. 1950 and was instead inducted into the Marine Corps as a Staff Sergeant, and went to Field Medical Service School at Camp Lejeune for eight weeks of training. By December of 1950, Martin was in Korea and assigned to the Charlie Medical unit, part of the 1st marine division. He was discharged from the Marine Corps in January of 1952.</p>
        </bioghist>
